  "annotation_notes": "The gene Rv3459c, also known as rpsK, encodes for ribosomal protein S11. The provided data includes a large number of publications (36) mentioning this gene. Most of these publications do not provide specific functional annotations for Rv3459c. A few publications mention the gene's role in infection and persistence, but without detailed mechanistic explanations. One publication (PMID: 272637175) notes the presence of MTB mRNA and DNA in respiratory samples, suggesting viable MTB may persist even after treatment. One publication (PMID: 38281181) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 41629493) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 41419821) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 40501622) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 34019733) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 34484145) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 31992637) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection. One publication (PMID: 19890396) mentions Rv3459c in the context of a study on the impact of host genetic variation on Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection.",
